III Proposed General DL Framework
In this section, we propose a general DL framework to learn the desired mapping in (P3). The proposed framework consists of two distinct models: a DVLN for discrete outputs and a CVLN for continuous outputs. These models are cascaded and trained jointly to provide near-optimal solutions while satisfying the constraints at the same time, as shown in Fig. 2. Specifically, the DVLN produces the support set of the discrete variable by . Subsequently, the continuous variable is produced by , where denotes the CVLN.
